title: La Barokka launches new music video
text:
Thursday, February 23, 2017, 19:02 La Barokka launches new music video Unbreakable - part of La Barokka's upcoming album 
Maria Muscat, La Barokka has launched her new music video, Unbreakable . 
The song penned by Matt Muxu Mercieca and composed and produced by Cyprian Cassar Somnio is meant to encourage people not to feel belittled if people in power tried to block their dreams and aspirations. 
La Barokka, a journalist with TVM, said it had been her dream to be filmed with real tigers, and she did this with the support of Christopher Borg, who owned several big cats at his park in Mtahleb. 
She said that as the video was being shot, she was nearly attacked by a tiger because she did not abide by Mr Borg’s instructions. 
Unbreakable is part of La Barokka's upcoming album. 
Her recent single Eternity was launched in October after an absence of six years in the music scene due to the death of her parents, that affected her singing and motivation for music.
